<s> "extensions" ... It is certainly not well-formed XML: no literal delimiters (" or ') on the attribute values.  </s>
<s> Also, there are empty elements in the head that do not use empty tags.  </s>
<s> It is not SGML or XML, because it uses comment delimiters to hide the script code.  </s>
<s> So it is "HTML with namespaces".  </s>
<s> But it uses the schema name as a namespace URI.  </s>
<s> It then becomes a small step to requiring the namespace name be a schema name (as Microsoft's BizTalk does) which in turn leads to "data capture": I have an article "How to Promote Organic Plurality on the WWW" about this issue, if anyone is interested, at http://www.ascc.net/xml/en/utf-8/monolith.html  </s>
